<Content>Honeymoon at Hiix We have just returned from a wonderful holiday at Hix Island House. We were given a very warm welcolme from the managers Diane,Michael and their right handwoman Brenda. When we were shown to our apartment- Loft one, we were not disappointed, it looked better in real life than on the web.We relaxed immediately,lazing by the pool or the swing bed. My favourite seat was the beautiful curved balcony from which I had a wonderful view of the island. The breakfast provided was great, the fresh bread was delicious,as was the local coffee, it was great hanging out in the mornings with out anyone knocking on the door to clean our room. Don't get me wrong, there was always someone around if you needed advise but guests are left to their own devises, which really suited us.Diane ,Michael and their team are great for helping out with local tips, they booked restaurants for us, pointed out the best beaches and even helped us when we were stopped by the police (it's a long story)!!The weekly cocktail party given by the owner was great fun,I don't advise driving afterwards! Thank you Hix House for such a memorable time,we'll be backLaura and Raechal London 
